article.headline: Ohio 69, Bowling Green 48
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Jerome Tillman scored 14 points and had eight rebounds to lead Ohio to a 69-48 win over Bowling Green on Tuesday night. Allen Hester added 12 points and Bubba Walther contributed 10 points for the Bobcats. Both teams had a slow first half, which ended tied at 22. Ohio (17-9, 8-5 Mid-American Conference) outscored Bowling Green by 21 points in the second half by shooting 56.7 percent (17-of-30) from the field, including 6-of-9 from behind the 3-point line. Bowling Green (11-14, 6-7) shot only 35.6 percent for the game and had 19 turnovers to Ohio's nine. Nate Miller and Joe Jakubowksi each scored 12 points for the Falcons. Miller had 9 rebounds.
